      "id": "E2-13-Q1",
      "type": "short-answer",
      "totalMarks": 4,
      "commandWord": "find",
      "difficulty": "easy",
      "questionText": "The functions $f$ and $g$ are defined as:\n$$f(x) = 3x - 1 \\quad \\text{and} \\quad g(x) = x^2 + 4$$\n\n(a) Find $f(5)$.\n(b) Find $g(-3)$.\n(c) Find $fg(2)$.\n(d) Find $gf(2)$.",
      "answerType": "expression",
      "correctAnswer": "(a) 14, (b) 13, (c) 23, (d) 29",
      "tolerance": null,
      "unit": null,
      "markScheme": [
        { "mark": "B1", "desc": "(a) $f(5)=3(5)-1=14$" },
        { "mark": "B1", "desc": "(b) $g(-3)=9+4=13$" },
        { "mark": "B1", "desc": "(c) $fg(2)=f(8)=3(8)-1=23$" },
        { "mark": "B1", "desc": "(d) $gf(2)=g(5)=25+4=29$" }
      ],
      "workingSteps": [
        "(a) $f(5)=3(5)-1=15-1=14$",
        "(b) $g(-3)=(-3)^2+4=9+4=13$",
        "(c) $g(2)=4+4=8$; $fg(2)=f(8)=3(8)-1=23$",
        "(d) $f(2)=3(2)-1=5$; $gf(2)=g(5)=25+4=29$"
      ],
      "explanation": "$fg(x)$ means apply $g$ first, then $f$; $gf(x)$ means apply $f$ first, then $g$."
    },
    {
      "id": "E2-13-Q2",
      "type": "short-answer",
      "totalMarks": 4,
      "commandWord": "find",
      "difficulty": "medium",
      "questionText": "The function $h(x) = \\dfrac{2x+1}{x-3}$ for $x \\neq 3$.\n\n(a) Find $h^{-1}(x)$.\n(b) Verify that $h(h^{-1}(x)) = x$.",
      "answerType": "expression",
      "correctAnswer": "(a) $h^{-1}(x) = \\dfrac{3x+1}{x-2}$",
      "tolerance": null,
      "unit": null,
      "markScheme": [
        { "mark": "M1", "desc": "Let $y=\\frac{2x+1}{x-3}$; rearrange: $y(x-3)=2x+1$" },
        { "mark": "M1", "desc": "$xy-3y=2x+1 \\Rightarrow xy-2x=3y+1 \\Rightarrow x(y-2)=3y+1$" },
        { "mark": "A1", "desc": "$x=\\frac{3y+1}{y-2}$, so $h^{-1}(x)=\\frac{3x+1}{x-2}$ cao" },
        { "mark": "A1", "desc": "Verification: $h\\left(\\frac{3x+1}{x-2}\\right)$ simplified to $x$" }
      ],
      "workingSteps": [
        "Let $y=\\frac{2x+1}{x-3}$",
        "$y(x-3)=2x+1$",
        "$xy-3y=2x+1$",
        "$xy-2x=3y+1$",
        "$x(y-2)=3y+1$",
        "$x=\\frac{3y+1}{y-2}$",
        "So $h^{-1}(x)=\\frac{3x+1}{x-2}$",
        "Verify: $h\\left(\\frac{3x+1}{x-2}\\right)=\\frac{2\\cdot\\frac{3x+1}{x-2}+1}{\\frac{3x+1}{x-2}-3}=\\frac{\\frac{6x+2+x-2}{x-2}}{\\frac{3x+1-3x+6}{x-2}}=\\frac{7x}{7}=x$ ✓"
      ],
      "explanation": "To find the inverse: swap $x$ and $y$ (or solve for $x$ in terms of $y$), then relabel."
    },
    {
